    "body": "### Problem\n\nAfter the 0.11.0 upgrade resizing causes glitchy behavior. In Kitty the layout is recalculated on resize. But in Kitty I got a segfault and the layout is messed up after quitting Neovim.\n\nIt looks like Neovim is not properly recalculating the layout after the resize. It's especially bad when I resize with Telescope open.\n\nThings seem substantially snappier though, so looking forward to the bugs being ironed out. ðŸ™‚ \n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Open iTerm\n2. nvim --clean\n3. Resize the window or pane\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe layout should reflow after the resize.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.0 Build type: Release LuaJIT 2.1.1741730670\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, 9.0\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 15.0.1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\niTerm 3.5.11, Kitty 3.5.11\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\niTerm: xterm-256color, Kitty: screen-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nHomebrew",
